{"lemma":"أَعَزَّيْ","slug":"أَعَزَّيْ","root":"ع.ز.ز","root_slug":"ع-ز-ز","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-ز-ز","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"أَعَزّ","root":"عزز","pos":"N","occurrence_count":3},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["adj","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":8},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n28929"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A3%D9%8E%D8%B9%D9%8E%D8%B2%D9%8E%D9%91%D9%8A%D9%92"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to cherish"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to love"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to treasure"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to strengthen"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to hold dear"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to respect"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"elative degree of عَزِيز (ʕazīz):; more powerful, stronger; most powerful, strongest"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"elative degree of عَزِيز (ʕazīz):; dearer; dearest"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Elative of عَزِيز (ʕazīz, “powerful, strong; dear”)."},"ipa":["/ʔa.ʕaz.za/","/ʔa.ʕazz/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n28929","headword_ar":"اَعَزُّ","root":"Ez","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"More,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"most, mighty, potent, powerful,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"strong:"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.: see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaziyzN","text_ar":"عَزِيزٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", of which it is the comparative and superlative form: and see an ex. voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aalo","text_ar":"اَلْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(p. 75): and another in a verse cited in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sb","text_ar":"صب"},{"kind":"text","text":", conj. 6]. It is related in a trad. of Aboo-Bekr, that he said to 'Áïsheh,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~a A^aHab~a","text_ar":"اـِنَّ اَحَبَّ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~aAsi A_ilaY~a ganFY A^anoti waA^aEaz~uhumo faqorFA A^anoti","text_ar":"النَّاسِ اـِلَىَّ غَنًى اَنْتِ وَاَعَزُّهُمْ فَقْرًا اَنْتِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily the one of mankind whose richness is most pleasing to me art thou; and the one of them whose poverty is most distressing to me art thou."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh.) The fem. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEaz~u","text_ar":"اَعَزُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as a noun of excess] is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Euz~aY","text_ar":"عُزَّى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, ISd, O, K;) like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuDolaY","text_ar":"فُضْلَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"is of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^afoDalu","text_ar":"اَفْضَلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (ISd.) [But see what follows.] ―         -b2-  ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEuz~aY","text_ar":"العُزَّى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"was the name of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain idol,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"belonging to Kureysh and Benoo-Kináneh:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain gum-acacia-tree,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samurapN","text_ar":"سَمُرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which the tribe of Ghatafán"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the son of Saad the son of Keys-'Eilán"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"used to worship;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the first who took it as an object of worship was Dhálim the son of As' ad; above Dhát- 'Irk, nine miles towards El-Bustán,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"at"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the valley called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"En-Nakhleh Esh-Shámeeyeh,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"near Mekkeh; or, as some say, at Et- Táïf:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) he, (K,) Dhálim, (O,) or they, (S,) built over it a house, (S, O, K) and named it"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bus~","text_ar":"بُسّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O, K,) accord. to Ibn-El-Kelbee; or, accord. to others,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bus~aA='","text_ar":"بُسَّا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;) and they appointed to it ministers, (S, TA,) like those of the Kaabeh; (TA;) and they used to hear in it a voice: (O, K, TA:) but Mohammad sent to it Khálid Ibn-El-Weleed, (S, O, K,) in the year of the conquest [of Mekkeh], (O, TA,) and he demolished the house, (S, K,) and slew the [chief] minister, (TA,) and burned the gum-acacia-tree: (S, O, K:) or, as is related on the authority of I'Ab,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain she-devil,"},{"kind":"text","text":"who used to come to three gumacacia-trees ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samuraAt","text_ar":"سَمُرَات"},{"kind":"text","text":") in Batn-Nakhleh, against whom Mohammad, when he conquered Mekkeh,"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2033},{"kind":"text","text":"sent Khálid Ibn-El-Weleed; and he cut down the trees, and slew her and her minister. (TA.) A poet says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"A^amaA wadimaA='K maAy^iraAtK taxaAluhaA\n                      \n                     \n                        EalaY qun~api AlEuz~aY wabiAln~asori EanodamaA"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"now surely, by bloods flowing, and running hither and thither, which thou wouldst think to be dragon's-blood, upon the mountain-top of El-' Ozzà, and by En-Nesr"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.) ISd says, I hold ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEuz~aY","text_ar":"العُزَّى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"to be fem. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^aEaz~u","text_ar":"الاَعَزُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and if so, the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al","text_ar":"ال"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the former is not redundant, but is like the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al","text_ar":"ال"},{"kind":"text","text":"in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHaArivu","text_ar":"الحَارِثُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEab~aAsu","text_ar":"العَبَّاسُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": but properly it should be redundant, because we have not heard"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEuz~aY","text_ar":"العُزَّى"},{"kind":"text","text":"as an epithet [of excess] like as we have heard"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlS~ugoraY","text_ar":"الصُّغْرَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlkuboraY","text_ar":"الكُبْرَى"},{"kind":"text","text":". (L, TA.) ―         -b3-  ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Euz~aY","text_ar":"عُزَّى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is [however] used in the sense of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaziyzapN","text_ar":"عَزِيزَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K, TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEaz~u","text_ar":"اَعَزُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[fem."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaz~aA='u","text_ar":"عَزَّا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is also syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaziyzN","text_ar":"عَزِيزٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which see in four places. (S, K.)"}],"source_refs":["S","O","K","TA"]}]}}